Use Case Diagram for E-Ticketing SystemA Use Case Diagram illustrates the high-level functional requirements of the system and how different users (Actors) interact with those functions (Use Cases).Actors:Customer: The end-user who purchases tickets.Validation Staff: The employee responsible for checking tickets at the venue.Event Organizer: The entity that manages and sells tickets for events.System Administrator: The user who manages the core system settings, reports, and user accounts.Use Cases:Use CaseDescriptionSearch Event/ServiceCustomer browses or searches for available events/services.View Event DetailsCustomer views information, dates, and ticket prices for an event.Select Ticket/SeatCustomer selects the desired type and quantity of tickets or specific seats.Make PaymentCustomer completes the transaction securely via a payment gateway.Generate E-TicketThe system automatically creates a unique digital ticket with a scannable code.View Past BookingsCustomer accesses their purchase history and ticket details.Validate TicketValidation Staff scans the E-Ticket to verify its authenticity for entry.Manage EventsEvent Organizer creates, updates, and sets pricing/capacity for events.View Sales ReportsEvent Organizer views performance metrics and sales data.Manage User AccountsSystem Administrator creates/modifies accounts and permissions.

